  "title": "A Valiant Rescue on Nar Shaddaa",
  "summary": "Amid a hostile takeover that has trapped everyone on Nar Shaddaa, the haggard, failing field medic Xar'on -- Doc Tanner -- limps into a ransacked weapons shop and finds the smuggler Captain Violet 'Allure' beaten nearly to death and delirious from an interrogation. Sent by Colonel Delede to find her, the exhausted doctor tends her wounds, gradually coaxes her back from a panic-stricken, language-scrambled haze, and half-carries her through the shadowed, war-torn streets to the makeshift field hospital he runs under CSA ESPO guard. There, despite repeatedly collapsing from his own ruined health, he sees Violet given a private bed, fresh treatment, food, and rest. As the sedatives ease her terror and her memories of the ordeal slowly settle, Violet -- comforted by the strangely familiar doctor -- learns of the Sith-backed takeover and the orders to extract her, and the two finally drift off to sleep together, the doctor watching over her as he holds her hand.",
